results.title: RewardPay Unlocks First-Ever Tax Pooling Payments with Rewards for New Zealand Businesses
results.description: AUCKLAND, New Zealand, Oct. 14, 2025 /PRNewswire/ -- Rewardpay.co.nz, the leading B2B fintech platform transforming how businesses pay suppliers and get rewarded, today announced a market-first: integrated tax pooling payments that reward businesses – a breakthrough in how tax pooling is managed. For the first time, businesses can make provisional tax payments directly to their preferred tax pooling provider through the RewardPay platform — earning valuable rewards while streamlining one of their largest financial obligations. This secure, seamless solution currently supports American Express payments, with additional payment options coming soon. Key Benefits for NZ Businesses: Earn rewards for paying tax: Earn American Express Membership Rewards® Points — and optionally, Air New Zealand Airpoints — on every tax pooling payment. Up to 55 days interest-free: Improve cash flow by leveraging extended credit terms through your American Express card. Tax pooling made easy: Enjoy streamlined access to leading tax pooling providers via embedded integrations within the RewardPay platform. "By connecting tax pooling payments directly to the RewardPay platform, we're making it faster, more secure, and — for the first time — rewarding. We're proud to partner with the industry leader TMNZ to bring this to market", said Mark Dawes, CEO of RewardPay. Matt Edwards, CEO of TMNZ, added: "As tax pooling pioneers, we're thrilled to partner with RewardPay to reimagine how businesses manage their tax obligations. This integration removes payment friction, enabling our clients to make provisional tax payments seamlessly using Amex — while also earning valuable rewards. It's a win for efficiency, flexibility, and financial performance." About RewardPay RewardPay is a leading B2B fintech platform transforming business payments into opportunities to earn rewards, enhance cash flow, and streamline operations. For over nine years, RewardPay has partnered with trusted global brands including American Express and Air New Zealand, and now New Zealand's top tax pooling providers to help businesses unlock value from everyday payments. www.rewardpay.co.nz About TMNZ TMNZ (Tax Management New Zealand) is the country's original and leading tax pooling provider, trusted by thousands of businesses and accountants for over 20 years. TMNZ empowers businesses to manage provisional tax with flexibility, reduce interest costs, and gain greater financial certainty. TMNZ is New Zealand's first registered tax pooling intermediary, known for its compliance expertise, innovation, and unwavering support of Kiwi businesses. RewardPay Media Contact:Chloe DawesHead of Marketing & Communicationchloe@rewardpay.com.au

results.title: Dewan Architects + Engineers Appointed Lead Architect and Interior Design Firm for Maia Ho Tram
results.description: HO CHI MINH CITY, Vietnam, Oct. 14, 2025 /PRNewswire/ -- Dewan Architects + Engineers has been appointed as the Lead Architect and Interior Design consultant for Maia Ho Tram, a landmark hospitality and residential development on Vietnam's southern coastline. Commissioned by Lodgis Hospitality Holdings in partnership with VinaLiving, the project will introduce a new era of wellness-oriented design to The Grand Ho Tram Strip, one of the region's largest integrated resorts. Maia Ho Tram is a landmark hospitality and residential development on Vietnam’s southern coast, designed by Dewan. Situated two hours from Ho Chi Minh City, Maia Ho Tram forms part of Zone A1 of Phase 3 of the resort's master plan. Dewan's design integrates a high-density hospitality and residential programme with a wellness-led ethos, capitalising on the site's oceanfront positioning while creating a strong sense of connection to its natural surroundings. A Vision for Wellness and Coastal Living Dewan's design narrative is centred on wellness and nature-driven principles. A cascading sequence of landscaped terraces and pools links the elevated podium to the beach, while a dramatic axial view connects the grand lobby to the sea. The development spans approximately 103,000 square metres, comprising two high-rise towers—Peace and Happy—a villa cluster, and a vibrant podium of shared amenities. The Peace Tower interiors are inspired by the "golden forest" concept, evoking the soft light filtering through trees at sunset. Villas arranged around a natural pond, podium-level leisure and dining options, and a rooftop wellness deck reinforce the development's focus on healthy, contemporary living. "Maia Ho Tram is a milestone project that reflects the values we bring to every commission: sustainability, lifestyle-driven design, and architectural innovation," said Ammar Al Assam, CEO of Dewan Architects + Engineers. "Vietnam and Southeast Asia are rapidly growing markets, and we are proud to contribute with a project that sets new benchmarks for wellness and hospitality, while creating long-term value for both residents and guests." Adding to this, Freek Jansen, Branch Manager of Dewan Southeast Asia, commented: "Our vision for Maia Ho Tram is to design more than just buildings—we are shaping an experience that brings people closer to nature while delivering the highest standards of contemporary living. It is a unique opportunity to strengthen our presence in Vietnam and demonstrate how design-led thinking can define new models of resort living." Integrated Lifestyle Experience The project includes a hotel operated by Fusion Hotel Group under the Maia Resort brand, 1,244 condominium apartments, and 36 low-rise villas. The podium will feature a seafood restaurant, two-level food court, kids' club, golf simulator, wellness centre, multifunctional hall for 400 people, and a beach club. The rooftop podium deck extends the resort lifestyle skyward with a lap pool, landscaped terraces, and fitness amenities. Two towers rising 31 and 32 floors are strategically oriented for panoramic views of the ocean, their skyline softened by terraced pocket gardens. Extensive glazing, vertical fins, and shading devices ensure efficiency and elegance in the tropical climate. Dewan will also oversee the implementation of Building Information Modeling (BIM), ensuring coordination across disciplines and precision in project delivery. Groundbreaking took place in April 2025, with construction now underway. Completion is scheduled for Q3 2027. About Dewan Architects + Engineers For over 40 years, Dewan Architects + Engineers has been at the forefront of the architecture and engineering industry in the Middle East, Asia, and beyond. Renowned for delivering innovative, sustainable, and people-centred designs, Dewan's portfolio spans hospitality, residential, commercial, education, and mixed-use sectors. With a multidisciplinary team and a commitment to design excellence, Dewan continues to shape transformative projects that redefine urban and cultural landscapes. For high-resolution photos, please download the media kit here. Maia Ho Tram is a landmark hospitality and residential development on Vietnam’s southern coast, designed by Dewan. results.title: ارتفاع أسعار الذهب مدعومة بتوقعات خفض أسعار الفائدة
creator: واس - سنغافورة
results.description: ارتفعت أسعار الذهب إلى مستوى قياسي اليوم، مدعومًا بتوقعات خفض أسعار الفائدة الأمريكية.وزاد الذهب في المعاملات الفورية بنسبة 0.4% ليصل إلى 4124.79 دولار للأوقية بحلول الساعة 0029 بتوقيت جرينتش، بعد أن سجل مستوى قياسيًا بلغ 4131.52 دولار في وقت سابق من الجلسة.فيما ارتفعت العقود الأمريكية الآجلة للذهب تسليم ديسمبر 0.3% إلى 4143.10 دولار.ارتفاع أسعار الفضةوفي المعاملات الفورية ارتفعت الفضة 0.3% إلى 52.49 دولار للأوقية، بعد أن سجلت 52.70 دولار في وقت سابق من اليوم.وبالنسبة للمعادن النفيسة الأخرى، ارتفع البلاتين 0.5% إلى 1653.45 دولار للأوقية.فيما ربح البلاديوم 1.6% إلى 1498.25 دولار مسجلًا أعلى مستوى منذ مايو 2023.
